      "role": "user",
      "content": "but why would the payload spike precisely during *deep focus*? that's when the neuro-electrical activity is most distinct. if you look at the encryption on these specific packets, it's not a standard TLS handshake, it's something way more proprietary and obfuscated, like it's trying to hide the content from any local network sniffers. it's almost like the OS is treating the user's cognitive state as a data source that needs to be covertly exfiltrated. if we assume for a second that this isn't just coincidence, doesn't it look like a massive, coordinated effort to use consumer hardware for something much more invasive than simple telemetry?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
